# 🚀 ARIA — Full Setup Guide (Clone → Run)

> Follow these steps **in order** on a fresh laptop to get the project running.

---

## 📋 Prerequisites to Install First

Your friend needs to install these **before** anything else:

| # | Software | Version | Download Link | Why It's Needed |
|---|----------|---------|---------------|-----------------|
| 1 | **Git** | Any | [git-scm.com](https://git-scm.com/) | To clone the repo |
| 2 | **Python** | 3.11+ | [python.org](https://www.python.org/downloads/) | Backend runs on Python |
| 3 | **Node.js** | 18+ | [nodejs.org](https://nodejs.org/) (LTS version) | Frontend runs on Node |
| 4 | **Ollama** | Latest | [ollama.com](https://ollama.com/) | Local AI model (LLM) |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> During **Python** installation, **check the box** that says **"Add Python to PATH"** — this is critical!
> During **Node.js** installation, the default options are fine.

---

## 🔧 Step-by-Step Setup

### Step 1: Clone the Repository

Open **Terminal / PowerShell / Command Prompt** and run:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/hacknova.git
cd hacknova
```

*(Replace `YOUR_USERNAME` with your actual GitHub username)*

---

### Step 2: Setup Ollama (AI Model)

After installing Ollama from the link above:

```bash
# Start Ollama (it may already be running as a service)
ollama serve

# In a NEW terminal, pull the AI model (downloads ~815MB)
ollama pull gemma3:1b
```

> [!NOTE]
> `gemma3:1b` is the lightweight model (~815MB). If the laptop has **8GB+ RAM**, you can also pull the better model:
> ```bash
> ollama pull gemma3:12b
> ```

**Verify Ollama is working:**
```bash
ollama list
```
You should see `gemma3:1b` in the output.

---

### Step 3: Setup the Backend (Python)

```bash
# Navigate to the backend folder
cd backend

# Create a virtual environment (recommended)
python -m venv venv

# Activate the virtual environment
# On Windows:
venv\Scripts\activate
# On Mac/Linux:
# source venv/bin/activate

# Install all Python dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Create the .env file from the template
copy .env.example .env
```

> [!TIP]
> The `.env.example` file has all the defaults pre-filled. For basic usage, you **don't need to change anything** — it will use Ollama with `gemma3:1b` by default.

**If you want to edit the `.env`** (optional):
```
OLLAMA_MODEL=gemma3:1b          # Change to gemma3:12b if you pulled it
OLLAMA_MODEL_FAST=gemma3:1b
OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
NCBI_API_KEY=                   # Optional: for PubMed searches
GEMINI_API_KEY=                 # Optional: legacy, not needed
```

---

### Step 4: Start the Backend

```bash
# Make sure you're in the backend/ folder with venv activated
uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000
```

You should see output like:
```
INFO:     Uvicorn running on http://0.0.0.0:8000 (Press CTRL+C to quit)
INFO:     Started reloader process
```

**Verify:** Open `http://localhost:8000` in a browser — you should see:
```json
{"name": "ARIA", "version": "1.0.0", "status": "running", "docs": "/docs"}
```

> [!WARNING]
> **Keep this terminal open!** The backend needs to stay running.

---

### Step 5: Setup & Start the Frontend (New Terminal)

Open a **new/second terminal** window:

```bash
# Navigate to the frontend folder (from the project root)
cd hacknova/frontend

# Install all Node.js dependencies
npm install

# Start the development server
npm run dev
```

You should see:
```
  VITE v5.3.1  ready in 500ms
  ➜  Local:   http://localhost:5173/
```

---

### Step 6: Open the App! 🎉

Open your browser and go to: **http://localhost:5173**

ARIA is now running! Ask it a research question and watch it work.

